definition.value: An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of trans-2-octenedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-acetamidofluorene compound in which the parent 2-acetamidofluorene is substituted on nitrogen by an acetoxy group.
The omega-oxo fatty acid obtained by oxygenation at position 26 of hexacosanoic acid.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of (S)-3-hydroxyoctanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is hexacosane in which the methyl groups have been oxidised to the corresponding carboxylic acids.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of 3-oxooctanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
A silyl ether that is isopropanol in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a trimethylsilyl group.

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of a sequence of one inosine, one guanosine, one cytidine, one 1-methylinosine and one uridine residue connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and with a phosphoric residue at the 3'-terminus..

An RNA oligonucleotide in which the RNA species is a tRNA molecule. An oligonucleotide that is a fragment of a larger tRNA molecule (either naturally occurring or synthetic). Phosphono groups may or may not be present at the 3'- and 5'- termini.
An alpha,omega dicarboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the carboxy groups of dodecanedioic acid.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of trans-2-dodecenedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
A delta-lactam that is 2-piperidone substituted at position 3 by an amino group.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of (S)-3-hydroxydodecanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of acetamides that is acetamide in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a 9H-fluoren-4-yl group.
Any steroid saponin that consists of a withanolide as the aglycone moiety.
An alpha,omega dicarboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the carboxy groups of decanedioic acid.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of 3-oxododecanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of trans-2-decenedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of (S)-3-hydroxydecanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that is the pentaanion of 3-oxodecanedioyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions; major species at pH 7.3.
A trihydroxyanthraquinone that is 9,10-anthraquinone which is substituted by a methyl substituent at C-3 and by hydroxy groups at C-1, C-2 and C-8.
A 3-(4-hydroxy-3,5-dimethoxyphenyl)prop-2-enoic acid in which the double bond has cis-configuration. It has been isolated from the shoots of alfalfa.
A silyl ether that is benzyl alcohol in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a trimethylsilyl group.
An alpha,omega dicarboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the carboxy groups of octanedioic acid.
A silyl ether that is 2,6-dihydroxypurine carrying three trimethylsilyl substituents at positions O-2, O-6 and N-7.

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of one inosine, one 1-methylated inosine, four cytidine, four guanosine and three uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-G-C-U-U-I-G-C-m(1)I-U-G-C-G and with a phosphoric residue at the 3'-terminus. It can exist in a hairpin structure, with hydrogen bonding linking the three complementary base pairs at each terminus.
An alpha-chloroketone that is acetanilide in the para- position is substituted by a chloroacetyl group.
An (S)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (3S,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-3-hydroxytetracosahexaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An aromatic ether that is 4-methoxyphenol in which one of the hydrogens ortho- to the methoxy group is replaced by a tert-butyl group.
An aromatic ether that is 4-methoxyphenol in which one of the hydrogens ortho- to the phenolic hydroxy group is replaced by a tert-butyl group.
A mixture of 2-tert-butyl-4-hydroxyanisole and 3-tert-butyl-4-hydroxyanisole. Is is used as an antioxidant and preservative in food, cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, rubber and petroleum products.
A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (2E,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-tetracosaheptaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

Any seco-steroid based on a 13,14-seco-16,24-cycloergostane skeleton and its substituted derivatives thereof. These phytochemicals form the major steroidal constituents of Physalis plants and exhibit antimicrobial and antiparasitic activity.

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of a sequence of adenosine, guanosine, inosine, 1-methylinosine and uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and with a phosphoric residue at the 3'-terminus..

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of one inosine, one 1-methylated inosine, three cytidine, three guanosine and three uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-U-U-I-G-C-m(1)I-U-G-C-G and with a phosphono group at the 3'-terminus.
A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (2E,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-tetracosahexaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of a sequence of adenosine, inosine, cytidine, 1-methylinosine and uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and with a phosphoric residue at the 3'-terminus.
An (S)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (3S,6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-3-hydroxytetracosapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z)-3-oxotetracosapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of a sequence of inosine, adenosine, guanosine, cytidine, 1-methylinosine and uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and with a phosphoric residue at the 3'-terminus.
A member of the class of  xanthones that is 9H-xanthen-9-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1, 2, 6 and 8.

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of a sequence of inosine, two adenosine, guanosine, cytidine, 1-methylinosine and uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and with a phosphoric residue at the 3'-terminus.

A tRNA oligonucleotide comprised of a sequence of inosine, three adenosine, guanosine, cytidine, 1-methylinosine and uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and with a phosphoric residue at the 3'-terminus.
A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide comprised of three deoxycytidine and three thymidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-C-T-T-T-C.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (R)-3-hydroxyicosanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (R)-3-hydroxystearoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (R)-3-hydroxybehenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An oligonucleotide comprised of fifteen thymidine residues connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (3R)-3-hydroxytetracosanoyl-CoA [(R)-3-hydroxylignoceroyl-CoA]; the major species at pH 7.3.
